The paper deals with the complexity of the Maximum Independent Set problem in various graph classes, which is a fundamental problem in computer science and graph theory. The paper uses techniques from computational complexity, graph theory, and approximation algorithms. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). Additionally, the paper involves some geometric arguments, which suggest the possibility of cs.CG (Computational Geometry) as a relevant sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with approximation algorithms, which could also place it in the cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) sub-category.
